{"id":20548,"date":"2024-01-29T18:36:23","date_gmt":"2021-03-29T13:06:23","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=20548"},"modified":"2023-01-04T11:45:37","modified_gmt":"2023-01-04T06:15:37","slug":"kitchen-cabinet-storage-ideas","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/kitchen-cabinet-storage-ideas\/","title":{"rendered":"Organised And Presentable: Kitchen Cabinet Storage Ideas For Your Home"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><em>Declutter your kitchen\u2019s working space and let it function to its fullest potential by implementing some easy and smart kitchen cabinet storage ideas. These ideas are applicable to both big and small kitchens alike<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>A kitchen is one of the most important rooms in the house as it feeds and nourishes us every day, and gives us the physical power to go on with our lives. So, it becomes essential to keep it organised, neat and presentable at all times. Kitchen cabinets play a major role in this context.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Kitchen cabinets help you store different types of things \u2014 crockery, cutlery, glasses, dishes and various food items \u2014 and they\u2019re extremely customisable according to the needs and preferences of the homeowners. Check out a few <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/kitchen-cabinet-design-ideas\/\">kitchen cabinet design ideas<\/a>. Add a few more <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/kitchen-storage-ideas\/\">kitchen storage hacks <\/a>to them and make the best use of your kitchen space.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You\u2019ll also be able to achieve the following with an organised kitchen cabinet storage:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>A greater sense of control over the kitchen and yourself as less visual clutter leads to less mental stress.<\/li><li>An easier workflow in the kitchen owing to the creation of custom kitchen zones.<\/li><li>An increased motivation to declutter the kitchen regularly to determine what to keep, replace or give away.&nbsp;<\/li><li>A better track of the products you have in the kitchen and their location so that you can avoid buying doubles.<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Kitchen cabinet storage comes in two forms: open kitchen cabinets and closed kitchen cabinets. Both of these have their own benefits and drawbacks.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Open Kitchen Cabinet Storage<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>It makes your kitchen feel more inviting and appear visually larger owing to open shelves.&nbsp;<\/li><li>It helps you make optimal use of the extra and often overlooked corners or spaces in your kitchen.&nbsp;<\/li><li>It allows you to constantly experiment with the looks of your kitchen as all the kitchen items in open kitchen cabinets act as decor elements.&nbsp;<\/li><li>It is also prone to the accumulation of a lot of dust over a period of time so you\u2019ll have to clean the open shelves thoroughly each week.&nbsp;<\/li><li>It can also lead to accidents if fragile items are kept within close reach of children and pets so be careful while organising the cabinets.&nbsp;<\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Closed Kitchen Cabinet Storage<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>It gives you the opportunity to make endless customisations to your kitchen depending upon the material and style you choose. For example, use steel kitchen cabinets for a more industrial modern look and dark wood kitchen cabinets for a traditional and classy look.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/li><li>It provides you with a more defined storage space where there is a specific place for everything.&nbsp;<\/li><li>It makes your kitchen look more neat and compact as these cabinets come with closed doors.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/li><li>It ensures the safety of your children and pets and also has a longer shelf life.&nbsp;<\/li><li>It is comparatively more expensive than open kitchen cabinet storage options.<\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Let\u2019s now look at some cool kitchen cabinet storage ideas that you can implement to keep your kitchen organised and on top of your game.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Design your modular kitchen that are smart like you\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/27152054\/design-modular-kitchens-that-are-smart-like-you.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">DIY Kitchen Cabinet Storage<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you\u2019re short on space in the kitchen but still want to make it decorative and functional, then this DIY kitchen cabinet storage idea is your ideal choice. You can stack and join\/glue together unused white wooden kitchen crates one on top of the other and create a customised open cabinet storage area for extra kitchen stuff that you don\u2019t frequently use. Not only does it look pretty but helps you make the most efficient use of available space.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183133\/diy-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea-.jpg\" alt=\"DIY kitchen cabinet storage made from unused wooden crates and stack on top of the other\" class=\"wp-image-20551\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183133\/diy-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea-.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183133\/diy-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea--300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183133\/diy-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea--768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183133\/diy-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea--150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Make use of deep drawer organisers to sort out and store your cutlery according to their shape and size, and also add a small to-do list hanging on the wall so that you can easily note down new recipes or grocery items that you need to buy<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Kitchen Cabinet Storage Ideas For Spices And Condiments<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>This kitchen cabinet storage idea of a wall-mounted spice rack with multiple shelves\/sections is perfect for those who always struggle with finding spices and condiments during the meal preparation process. You can neatly label all the containers\/jars and logically place them so that it becomes easier for you to access them the next time. It also makes the kitchen look sleek and compact.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183126\/corner-kitchen-cabinet-storage-ideas-for-spices.jpg\" alt=\"Wall mounted storage cabinets for kitchen with multiple shelves\" class=\"wp-image-20550\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183126\/corner-kitchen-cabinet-storage-ideas-for-spices.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183126\/corner-kitchen-cabinet-storage-ideas-for-spices-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183126\/corner-kitchen-cabinet-storage-ideas-for-spices-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183126\/corner-kitchen-cabinet-storage-ideas-for-spices-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>An additional tip that you can use is to turn the food labels in a way that they\u2019re always facing out and are clearly visible<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Modern Kitchen Cabinet Storage Ideas<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>This modern kitchen cabinet storage idea in dull red and stainless steel looks very stylish and luxurious. You can install a hanging rack with hooks above the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/kitchen-island-designs-for-home\/\">kitchen island<\/a> to place all your kitchen cutlery, small mugs, cups and cooking implements. Alternatively, you can also use the base of the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/kitchen-chimney-designs\/\">kitchen chimney<\/a> as a shelf to place items (as in the picture). An open cabinet on one end can be used to stack glassware and a pan rack on the other end to slide in dishes vertically.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183145\/modern-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea.jpg\" alt=\"Modern kitchen cabinet storage idea in dull red and stainless steel\" class=\"wp-image-20553\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183145\/modern-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183145\/modern-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183145\/modern-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183145\/modern-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Cooking caddies and customisable knife blocks are the latest trends in kitchen storage. They\u2019re easy to access and convenient to use and fit perfectly in any corner of the kitchen area<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe title=\"The Secret to Trendy Kitchen Cabinets in 2024\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/CrIs1mWQD5U?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Showcase-Style Kitchen Cabinet Storage<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>This showcase-style kitchen cabinet storage idea has glass cabinets and a pair of side shelves which allow you to display mason jars and small containers of seeds, nuts and spices in a colour-coordinated and presentable way.&nbsp; They also make navigating in this kitchen a lot easier as the space is smartly divided into activity-specific zones. Food ingredients are stored above the workstation so that the countertop space can be optimally used to prepare food.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183151\/showcase-style-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea.jpg\" alt=\"Showcase-style kitchen cabinet storage  with glass cabinets and a pair of side shelves\" class=\"wp-image-20554\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183151\/showcase-style-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183151\/showcase-style-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183151\/showcase-style-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183151\/showcase-style-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>This kitchen cabinet storage style lends a warm and rustic look to the kitchen and is accentuated by the task and accent lights underneath.  It also creates a sense of uniformity in the space<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Small Kitchen Storage Cabinet<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Apart from a creative combination of open and closed kitchen cabinet storage spaces, you can also make use of wicker baskets in the kitchen to store fresh fruits and veggies. They not only look chic and visually appealing but are also practical and durable in nature, and allow your fresh stock to breathe freely. The row of wooden lofts on the top makes a perfect addition to this kitchen and can be used to store food items and utensils which aren\u2019t that frequently used.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183157\/small-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea.jpg\" alt=\"Combination of open and closed small kitchen cabinet storage\" class=\"wp-image-20555\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183157\/small-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183157\/small-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183157\/small-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183157\/small-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>This kind of small kitchen cabinet storage idea helps to keep your kitchen clutter-free and visually pleasing<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Get a Free Modular Kitchen Worth \u20b92 Lakhs with Your Home Interiors.\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/08183703\/designcafe-offer-free-modular-kitchen-worth-2-lakhs.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Tall Kitchen Cabinet Storage Ideas<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>This tall kitchen cabinet serves as a pseudo larder unit that stores many different kitchen items, large kitchen appliances and extra grocery supplies in a space-saving and tidy manner. You can store your most-used food supplies on the lower shelves, small knickknacks on the upper shelves and some small green potted plants on the top to add a pop of colour and freshness in the kitchen.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183203\/tall-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea.jpg\" alt=\"A tall kitchen cabinet storage idea with a translucent glass door\" class=\"wp-image-20556\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183203\/tall-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183203\/tall-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183203\/tall-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183203\/tall-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>The translucent doors on this tall kitchen cabinet allow you to see the contents stocked inside without opening the cabinet itself, which is quite convenient at times<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Also Read: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/kitchen-design-for-elderly\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">How To Organize A Kitchen For The Elderly<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Upper-Corner Kitchen Cabinet Storage<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>These upper-corner kitchen cabinet storage ideas make efficient use of the often-overlooked space in the kitchen. It is usually smaller than the standard kitchen cabinets but perfect to store small jars and bottles. It breaks the usual monotony in the kitchen and adds some visual interest to the space.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183209\/upper-corner-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea.jpg\" alt=\"Corner kitchen cabinet storage without a door makes efficient use of space\" class=\"wp-image-20557\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183209\/upper-corner-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183209\/upper-corner-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183209\/upper-corner-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/29183209\/upper-corner-kitchen-cabinet-storage-idea-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>You can also use these corner kitchen cabinets to store your fragile glassware, and the best way to do that is to alternate the direction in which you keep your wine glasses so that more space is created on the shelves for other items <\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>That\u2019s all there is! Hope this blog post has provided you with plenty of actionable tips to effectively organise your kitchen cabinet storage. Also, if you\u2019re planning to design a modern and multifunctional kitchen cabinet storage for your living space, then <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/\">DesignCafe<\/a> is the ultimate one-stop destination to fulfil your dreams.<\/p>\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n                    \n    <h3 class=\"widget-title text-dark text-center mb-0\">Looking For Modular Kitchens At Best Prices<\/h3>\n  \n \n     <p class=\"text-center text